pilotsr and ryangt1:

This is the Wilco CRJ 2004 CD ROM.  All manuals and movies are
included.  WinRAR should produce a file called "crj200410_snp.iso".
Use Nero or Alcohol to mount this disc image or burn onto a CD.
The CD should autostart. Use Serial 2JPWV6-BD5ZM64E-TVB772H

Hope this helps.  The CD comes with some extras, too, including a 20 minute tutorial video as well as a 30-minute JustPlanes CRJ vid.  Great package, and a great post.  Seed it for others as it's a worthwhile aircraft.

BritneysOrifice, thanks so much!  That number worked like a charm.  It took me so long to get my hands on this bird I was a bit disappointed when it didn't include a #.  You just made my day, and i'm sure many others as well.

Cheers from NY :)

He guys, can someone explane me clearly how I can mount an image with Deaom tools?
It would REALLY help me!:-)

PHBFO I am willing to help you. First after you run the program there should be a Daemon Tools program on the bottom right. Near the time. Then right-click the program and go to Virtual CD/DVD-ROM. A new bar should pop up and go to Device 0: [E:] No media. Another bar should pop up and go to Mount Image. Find the .ISO file and click Open. There you go.
